cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.CY 

This paper presents techniques for visualizing and exploring large quantities of microblogging data, which involves aspects of information retrieval (IR), natural language processing (NLP), human-computer interaction (HCI), and cybernetics (CY). The paper also includes a user study to evaluate the effectiveness of the visualization techniques, which falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.HC, and cs.CY.
